HEADWORD: Atman
<hw>At"man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Skr.
<ets>⟦amac⟧tman</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Hinduism)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>The life principle, soul, or individual essence.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>The universal ego from whom all individual atmans arise. This sense
is a European excrescence on the East Indian thought.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

